5. Domain Routing Engine (Conceptual)

Goal:

Select minimum sufficient domains

Rule:
Use the fewest domains needed to explain + act.


⸻

Routing Heuristics

Trigger Conditions

High intensity / load        → physics, biology
Multiple signals             → systems, math
Low energy                  → economics, biology
High stress                 → psychology, cybernetics
Repetition                  → history, memetics
Timing disruption           → music
High workload               → business, economics
Conflict                    → strategy, game theory
Meaning-seeking language    → philosophy, myth
Feedback loop language      → cybernetics


⸻

Output

Selected Domains = ranked subset of all domains


⸻

6. Interpretation Layer

Each selected domain produces:

{
  domain: X,
  summary: "domain-specific interpretation",
  signal: low | medium | high,
  evidence: [...]
}


⸻

Example (Physics)

"Load is concentrated in the upper system, indicating pressure accumulation."

Example (Economics)

"Energy expenditure exceeds available capacity."

Example (Myth)

"This pattern resembles a burden-bearing loop becoming part of the user’s story."


⸻

7. Action Synthesis

Actions are generated based on:
	•	domain overlap
	•	signal strength
	•	cross-domain agreement

⸻

Action Rules

If biology + music → fix recovery timing
If physics + systems → relieve highest load node
If economics + business → reduce scope / reallocate effort
If cybernetics → interrupt loop
If history → compare past triggers
If psychology → separate signal from interpretation


⸻

Output

Top N prioritized actions


⸻

8. Confidence Model

High confidence:
  ≥2 high-signal domains OR strong cross-domain agreement

Medium:
  mixed signals

Low:
  weak or sparse data


⸻

9. Memory Layer (EchoFrame)

Each execution produces:

snapshot → interpretation → delta → compressed memory


⸻

Memory Invariants

- reversible compression
- preserve signal over noise
- retain failure cases
- track recurrence patterns


⸻

10. Daemon Mapping

Daemon	Function
Spider	graph / relation mapping
Hound	anomaly detection
Mirror	invariant + ethics check
Conductor	domain routing / orchestration
EchoFrame	temporal compression


⸻

11. Guardrails (Critical)

1. No domain overrides reality
2. Myth is symbolic, not literal
3. Compression must remain reversible
4. Avoid overfitting (too many domains)
5. Always separate:
   - signal
   - interpretation
   - narrative


